Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Trim the @Aubergine{2}, then slice into rounds approximately 1cm thick. Pop the rounds onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer (use two #baking trays{} if necessary).

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the potato chunks onto another large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer (use two baking trays if necessary).

Roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While everything roasts, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the garlic and stir-fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Harissa Paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{50%ml} for the sauce.

> The Harissa Paste amount can be adjusted if you'd prefer things milder.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir the @Butter{20%grams} through the sauce until melted.

Spoon half of the tomato sauce into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and spread out in an even layer. Lay half of the roasted aubergine rounds on top, then sprinkle over half of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams}.

Repeat this once more with the remaining sauce, aubergine and cheese - parmigiana made!

When the potatoes have about ~{10%minutes} left, bake the parmigiana on the top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{8-10%minutes}.

When your parmigiana is ready, allow to stand for a couple mins before serving.

Share between your plates with the roast potatoes and @Wild Rocket{20%grams} leaves alongside.

Drizzle the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} over the leaves to finish. Enjoy!